`crates/ctx-context/src` is the whole `ctx-context` binary: it computes, dedups, and renders the chain of `.ctx`/`intent.md`/rollup files an agent needs before touching a path, and delivers it two ways — a `--hook` mode that injects `additionalContext` after Claude Code tool calls, and a direct-path CLI mode for manual invocation. Depending on this crate gets you `cli::dispatch` (the sole library entry point besides `hook::run`) and nothing else; internals are not meant to be called piecemeal.

The core pipeline is linear and each stage owns one concern: `repo_path.rs` validates untrusted path strings into safe segment lists (the only gate untrusted input passes through); `chain.rs` turns a validated `RepoPath` into an ordered list of rollup/intent/leaf node locations (order and `NodeKind::label()` values are a protocol other stages rely on); `serve.rs` resolves that node list to actual text, treating absent files as soft markers, and layers session-scoped deduplication (`fresh_chain_for`) on top via `session.rs`'s per-session served-set ledger; `hook.rs` and `cli.rs` are the two callers of `serve::fresh_chain_for`/`serve::render`, and must stay in lockstep on `session::ENV_SESSION_ID` and the `Option<Vec<Node>>` "nothing new" convention. `env.rs`'s `Env` trait is the filesystem/env-var boundary that `chain`, `serve`, `session`, and `hook` are all written against instead of `std::fs`, enabling in-memory test fakes; `error.rs` supplies the shared `CtxError` taxonomy used throughout instead of `anyhow`/`Box<dyn Error>`. `main.rs` is the only place process-level I/O (argv, stdin, exit codes) happens; `lib.rs` just declares the module tree.

Invariants spanning the subtree: hook mode (`hook::run`, and transitively anything it calls) must never error or panic — all failures degrade to empty string or a `(...unavailable...)` marker string, checked in both `hook.rs` and `session::load`'s fail-open loading. Session dedup persists served-node state even when the caller fails to display the result (no rollback), so `serve.rs` and `session.rs` must be edited together for ledger-format changes. Changing `chain::NodeKind`/`ChainNode` requires updating `serve.rs`'s rendering and node-filtering logic in lockstep.